  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2007-10-31",
    "date": "2007-11-21T21:59:48Z",
    "text": "Children's Chemical Risk Reduction Act - Requires any children's product or child care article that contains a phthalate to be treated as a banned hazardous substance under the Federal Hazardous Substances Act. Applies certain prohibitions of that Act to such product article.\n\nProvides that, if a manufacturer modifies a children's product or child care article that contains a phthalate to comply with such ban, it shall: (1) use an alternative to phthalates that is the least toxic; and (2) not use any of specified prohibited alternatives to phthalates."
  },
